@* ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
   HOW IT WORKS
   ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ *@
<section id="how" class="section" style="scroll-margin-top: 80px">
    <div class="inner">
        <div class="section-eyebrow">How it works</div>
        <h2>From headline to trade in seconds.</h2>
        <p class="section-lead">
            Every time the bot wakes up, it grabs the latest news for every ticker you follow.
            It asks an AI whether the story is actually a catalyst. If the answer survives all
            your safety checks, the bot places a market order through Alpaca. That's the whole loop.
        </p>

        <div class="flow">
            <div class="step">
                <div class="icon">📰</div>
                <h4>1. Read the news</h4>
                <p>Pulls the latest stories from Finnhub, SEC filings, insider trades, Google News,
                and Fed announcements all at once.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="arrow">→</div>
            <div class="step">
                <div class="icon">🧠</div>
                <h4>2. Decide what matters</h4>
                <p>Google's Gemini classifies each headline as bullish, bearish, or noise, with a
                confidence score. Macro context from prediction markets and the Fed gets mixed in too.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="arrow">→</div>
            <div class="step">
                <div class="icon">⚡</div>
                <h4>3. Place the trade</h4>
                <p>If the signal clears all your safety gates, an order goes to your Alpaca paper
                account in seconds. Your dashboard updates live with positions, P&amp;L, and the reason for every trade.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

@* ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
   PRODUCT DETAILS — three tabs replacing the old Coverage / Safety / Features sections.
   The #features anchor (used by the nav menu) sits on the section so menu links still scroll
   to it, then the JS at the bottom auto-activates the matching tab if the URL has #coverage,
   #safety, or #features.
   ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ *@
<section id="features" class="section dark" style="scroll-margin-top: 80px">
    <div class="inner">
        <div class="section-eyebrow">What's inside</div>
        <h2>The bot, the gates, the replay trail.</h2>
        <p class="section-lead">
            The data it reads, the gates that protect you, and the tools that help you understand what happened. Tap any tab.
        </p>

        <div class="tabs" role="tablist">
            <button class="tab active" data-tab="coverage" role="tab" aria-selected="true">📡 Coverage</button>
            <button class="tab" data-tab="safety" role="tab" aria-selected="false">🛡️ Safety</button>
            <button class="tab" data-tab="capabilities" role="tab" aria-selected="false">⚙️ Features</button>
        </div>

        @* ─── Coverage tab ───────────────────────────────────────────────── *@
        <div class="tab-panel active" data-panel="coverage" role="tabpanel">
            <p class="dim" style="margin-bottom:20px;font-size:14px">
                One feed can miss things, so we use eight. The more angles the bot has on a story, the harder it is for important news to slip past you.
            </p>
            <div class="source-grid">
                <div class="source"><div class="ic">📡</div><div class="body"><strong>Finnhub per-ticker</strong><span>Real-time company news for every ticker you follow.</span><span class="free">Included</span></div></div>
                <div class="source"><div class="ic">🏛️</div><div class="body"><strong>SEC EDGAR filings</strong><span>Official 8-K, 10-Q, and 10-K filings as they hit the SEC.</span><span class="free">Included</span></div></div>
                <div class="source"><div class="ic">👤</div><div class="body"><strong>Insider trades</strong><span>When executives buy or sell their own stock.</span><span class="free">Included</span></div></div>
                <div class="source"><div class="ic">🌐</div><div class="body"><strong>Google News</strong><span>Reuters, MarketWatch, Yahoo, Bloomberg, and dozens more.</span><span class="free">Included</span></div></div>
                <div class="source"><div class="ic">🧠</div><div class="body"><strong>Anthropic Claude verification</strong><span>Optional Claude check with live web_search before a potential buy.</span><span class="paid">Configurable</span></div></div>
                <div class="source"><div class="ic">🐦</div><div class="body"><strong>Grok X-trending</strong><span>Optional live X/Twitter search for trending tickers.</span><span class="paid">Configurable</span></div></div>
                <div class="source"><div class="ic">🎯</div><div class="body"><strong>Manifold odds</strong><span>Prediction-market odds feeding into every prompt.</span><span class="free">Included</span></div></div>
                <div class="source"><div class="ic">🏦</div><div class="body"><strong>Fed events</strong><span>Press releases and speeches from the Federal Reserve.</span><span class="free">Included</span></div></div>
            </div>
            <p class="dim" style="text-align:center;font-size:12px;margin-top:18px">
                Self-hosted users bring their own API keys. Managed instances can include provider setup and operations.
            </p>
        </div>

        @* ─── Safety tab ─────────────────────────────────────────────────── *@
        <div class="tab-panel" data-panel="safety" role="tabpanel">
            <p class="dim" style="margin-bottom:20px;font-size:14px">
                One bullish headline is never enough. Every potential buy passes through up to five gates, cheapest first. Most signals get filtered out long before they reach the broker.
            </p>
            <div class="gate-stack">
                <div class="gate-row"><div class="num">1</div><div class="meta"><strong>Sentiment + confidence gate</strong><span>The AI has to come back bullish, actionable, and above your confidence threshold. You can raise or lower it.</span></div><div class="cost">Core</div></div>
                <div class="gate-row"><div class="num">2</div><div class="meta"><strong>Confirmation window</strong><span>The bot waits for matching signals on the same ticker before pulling the trigger.</span></div><div class="cost">Core</div></div>
                <div class="gate-row"><div class="num">3</div><div class="meta"><strong>Earnings blackout</strong><span>No trades within your configured window around scheduled earnings.</span></div><div class="cost">Core</div></div>
                <div class="gate-row"><div class="num">4</div><div class="meta"><strong>Grok second opinion</strong><span>Optional live X and web search to look for contradicting evidence before a buy.</span></div><div class="cost">Optional</div></div>
                <div class="gate-row"><div class="num">5</div><div class="meta"><strong>Claude verification</strong><span>Optional web_search reasoning check that can approve, caution, or veto the trade.</span></div><div class="cost">Optional</div></div>
            </div>
            <p class="dim" style="text-align:center;font-size:12px;margin-top:16px">
                On top of that: position size cap, daily loss kill switch, max trades per day, pending-order-aware sizing. All built in.
            </p>
        </div>

        @* ─── Features tab ───────────────────────────────────────────────── *@
        <div class="tab-panel" data-panel="capabilities" role="tabpanel">
            <p class="dim" style="margin-bottom:20px;font-size:14px">
                Everyone runs the same underlying bot, but you control how yours behaves. Set a ticker blacklist, block bad-news keywords, boost good ones, and define when your bot is allowed to trade. Your bot will look nothing like anyone else's.
            </p>
            <div class="feature-grid">
                <div class="feature"><div class="icon">🎚️</div><h4>Every threshold is yours</h4><p>Minimum confidence, max position size, daily loss limit, max trades per day, exit percentages. Tune anything.</p></div>
                <div class="feature"><div class="icon">🚫</div><h4>Personal trading rules</h4><p>Tickers to never buy. Keywords that block a trade. Keywords that boost confidence. Hours when the bot is allowed to open positions. Minimum hold time. Make your bot truly yours.</p></div>
                <div class="feature"><div class="icon">🛑</div><h4>Five exit strategies</h4><p>Hard stop loss, trailing stop with peak tracking, take profit, max hold time, bearish news exit. Mix and match.</p></div>
                <div class="feature"><div class="icon">🔭</div><h4>Dynamic ticker discovery</h4><p>The bot watches the broader news firehose for unusual buzz and promotes high-mention tickers onto a temporary watchlist for extra scanning.</p></div>
                <div class="feature"><div class="icon">📊</div><h4>Live dashboard + reports</h4><p>Account equity, open positions with live P&amp;L, every order, every AI decision, an equity curve for the last week, and lifetime win rate stats.</p></div>
                <div class="feature"><div class="icon">⏪</div><h4>Replay backtesting</h4><p>Replay stored decisions, submitted orders, and price snapshots against shadow portfolios to see which gates helped or hurt.</p></div>
                <div class="feature"><div class="icon">🪙</div><h4>Paper money, real workflow</h4><p>Alpaca's paper environment mirrors the real market. Same order routing, same fills, same data. Practice with $100,000 of paper without spending a dollar.</p></div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

<script>
    // Tab switcher for the three-tab product section. Also reads the URL hash on load
    // so deep links like /#safety land on the right tab. The nav menu still uses #features
    // which corresponds to the third tab (capabilities).
    (function() {
        var tabs = document.querySelectorAll('.tabs .tab');
        if (!tabs.length) return;
        function activate(name) {
            tabs.forEach(function(t) {
                var on = t.dataset.tab === name;
                t.classList.toggle('active', on);
                t.setAttribute('aria-selected', on ? 'true' : 'false');
            });
            document.querySelectorAll('.tab-panel').forEach(function(p) {
                p.classList.toggle('active', p.dataset.panel === name);
            });
        }
        tabs.forEach(function(t) { t.addEventListener('click', function() { activate(t.dataset.tab); }); });
        // Deep-link support: /#coverage, /#safety, /#features (alias for capabilities)
        var hash = (location.hash || '').replace('#', '').toLowerCase();
        if (hash === 'features') activate('capabilities');
        else if (hash === 'coverage' || hash === 'safety') activate(hash);
    })();
</script>

