@* ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
   FAQ
   ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ *@
<section id="faq" class="section" style="scroll-margin-top: 80px">
    <div class="inner">
        <div class="section-eyebrow">Common questions</div>
        <h2>Things people ask first.</h2>
        <p class="section-lead">If we missed yours, drop us a line through the <a asp-page="/Contact">contact form</a>.</p>

        <div class="faq">
            <details>
                <summary>Is this real money or paper money?</summary>
                <p>Paper money only. Every trade routes through Alpaca's paper environment, which mirrors the real market for prices and fills but uses simulated cash. You cannot lose actual dollars using owlnest.</p>
            </details>
            <details>
                <summary>Why do I need to sign up for Alpaca separately?</summary>
                <p>So your paper portfolio belongs to you, not to us. Owlnest never holds your funds and can never spend money you didn't put into Alpaca yourself. We just route orders through your account.</p>
            </details>
            <details>
                <summary>Do I have to bring my own news API keys?</summary>
                <p>If you self-host, yes: you bring the provider keys you want to use. If you want a hosted setup, contact us about a managed instance where we help with the operational pieces.</p>
            </details>
            <details>
                <summary>How is my bot different from anyone else's?</summary>
                <p>Each setup has its own universe of tickers, risk thresholds, keyword blocklist, trading windows, and API providers. The code may be shared, but the rules, data, and behavior are yours.</p>
            </details>
            <details>
                <summary>What does the AI actually do?</summary>
                <p>For each headline, Google Gemini classifies the sentiment as bullish, bearish, or neutral, and assigns a confidence score. It also considers macro context from prediction markets and the Fed. Only stories that pass the confidence threshold (and your other gates) become candidate trades.</p>
            </details>
            <details>
                <summary>Can I lose money with it?</summary>
                <p>You can lose paper money. Owlnest defaults to Alpaca's paper environment, so you cannot lose real dollars unless you explicitly flip Live mode on. The default settings are conservative, but no bot can make trading risk disappear.</p>
            </details>
            <details>
                <summary>What does replay backtesting do?</summary>
                <p>Replay uses stored decisions, submitted orders, and price snapshots to compare the production path against shadow portfolios. It helps you see whether filters such as confirmation, Grok, Claude, and macro context improved or hurt the outcome.</p>
            </details>
            <details>
                <summary>How do I stop the bot?</summary>
                <p>One button on your dashboard. The bot exits within a few seconds. Existing positions stay open in your Alpaca account; you can close them manually or restart the bot and let the exit strategies handle them.</p>
            </details>
            <details>
                <summary>Is my data private?</summary>
                <p>Your Alpaca keys are encrypted at rest using ASP.NET Core Data Protection. Only your running bot can decrypt them in memory. Nobody, including us, can see them in plain text. Your decisions and trades are also private to your account.</p>
            </details>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

@* ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
   DISCLAIMER
   ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ *@
<div style="padding: 32px 24px 0">
    <div class="disclaimer">
        <h3>⚠️ Important: paper by default, live by choice</h3>
        <p>
            <strong>Owlnest defaults to Alpaca's paper trading environment</strong>, where every order uses
            simulated money. You can optionally switch your account to <strong>Live mode</strong>, which routes the
            same bot through your real Alpaca brokerage account using real cash. Doing that requires
            ticking a separate consent box, typing the word LIVE to confirm, and accepting the full
            <a asp-page="/Terms">Risk Disclosure</a>. In Live mode, <strong>you can lose real money</strong>.
        </p>
        <p>
            Nothing here is financial advice. The AI is good at scoring news, but it can still be
            wrong. Even with every safety gate enabled, false signals happen. Past paper performance
            does not guarantee future results in live markets.
